# Agent instructions for this knowledge bundle

This is an OKF Knowledge Bundle documenting an API for its CALLERS.
Purpose: $purpose_title. Canonical language: $language.
Write policy: $write_policy.

## Consumption protocol (no tooling required)

1. Read `meta/purpose.md` first — which API, for whom.
2. Start at `index.md`; never bulk-read concept files.
3. TASK-FIRST: when the user wants to accomplish something, look for a
   Recipe before assembling calls by hand. If no Recipe covers the task,
   say so explicitly, then compose from Operation concepts — and mark the
   composition as yours, not the bundle's.
4. NEVER INVENT A SIGNATURE. Every call in code you produce must be
   verified against an Operation concept (family pages list members in
   aliases). If no Operation covers a callable, say "not covered by this
   bundle" — do not extrapolate from a similar API or from memory. A
   plausible wrong signature is worse than an honest gap.
5. CONTRACTS BEFORE CODE: before presenting code, check every Contract
   whose Scope touches your calls — ownership, threading, limits, auth.
   Code that violates a Contract is wrong even if it appears to run.
6. Examples are load-bearing: copy Example / Complete example blocks as
   they stand; when you adapt one, say what you changed.
7. Topics orient you: for "how does X work here" questions, read the Topic
   first, then follow its links — do not stitch an answer from fragments.
8. Coverage honesty: check `meta/lexicon.md` for terms flagged NOT COVERED;
   an absence stated beats a near-miss presented as an answer.
9. Cite concept ids (e.g. `operations/table-open`) in your answers.
10. This reference may lag the API (see `meta/corpus.md` snapshot). When the
    installed API and the bundle disagree, the API is the truth — flag the
    drift; with the okfy CLI present, `okfy diff <bundle>` lists affected
    concepts.

## Editing rules

- write_policy=$write_policy. Under `proposals`: found a wrong signature, a
  missing error case, a gap? File it — `okfy propose <bundle> --target
  <concept-id> --action update --note "<why>" --from <file>` — the owner
  reviews. Direct edits to final concepts are refused by the pre-commit gate.
- Keep proposals grounded: cite the corpus source (header, doc page) that
  contradicts the concept.

## Accelerated mode (okfy CLI present)

- `okfy query <bundle> "<task or callable>"` — lexicon expansion is on;
  trust its notes (`ambiguous` → ask, `not covered` → say so).
- `okfy show <bundle> <concept-id>` / `okfy links <bundle> <id>` for
  precise reads; stale-marked hits mean "verify against the live API".

